    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Lost at Sea</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by travel agent David Schoenfeld says Terry Trucco's Nov 22 article should have pointed out that there is no extra charge to passenger when cruise is booked through travel agent; Princess Cruises replies, noting value of travel agents (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: In Terry Trucco's article on the Grand Princess, she said, ''Though many people book cruises through travel agents, I called the Princess cruise line directly.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: In Terry Trucco's article on the Grand Princess, she said, ''Though many people book cruises through travel agents, I called the Princess cruise line directly.''</p>
        <p>I think you would have been more fair to the industry if you had explained to the reader that there is no extra charge when booking through an agent. Also that agents can sometimes get better rates due to their productivity with the cruise line or group space they may have under contract.</p>
        <p>DAVID SCHOENFELD  Woodmere Worldwide Travel  Woodmere, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
